description:
&lt;p&gt;Kingston Hospital Trust are seeking experienced Clinical Ultrasound Sonographer&#39;s to join the Bank to assist with the current pandemic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To provide a comprehensive, quality sonographic service to a variety of inpatient and outpatient client groups. To maintain the highest standards of care for all patients undergoing sonographic examinations within the radiology and maternity service, whilst promoting a high standard of technical expertise within all relevant clinical areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To perform and independently report the following ultrasound examinations; obstetric including gynaecological (TA and TV) early pregnancy, abdominal, small parts and vascular including complex Doppler techniques.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we need from you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· NMC Registration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Proven experience working in Clinical Ultrasound&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During this pandemic we are fastracking our recruitment process but will still require:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Proof of Right to Work in the UK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· An Enhanced DBS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Occupational Health Clearance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this role please complete the application box below and attach your CV&lt;/p&gt;
